-- Sanofi declines comment on possible BMS deal
-- 
-- Tue Mar 27, 2007 4:58am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/03/27/us-sanofi-bristolmeyers-comment-idUSL2711507120070327

 

 PARIS  (Reuters) - French pharmaceuticals group Sanofi ( SASY.PA ) on Tuesday declined comment on an article in Times newspaper suggesting the group was looking at a merger with Bristol-Myers Squibb ( BMY.N ). 

 The spokesman however denied there was a divergence of views between chairman Jean-Francois Le Hecq and chief executive Gerard le Fur, as the Times reported. There have been regular rumors about a friendly tie-up between the two groups to create a global drugs giant.